Security Features

The project includes several security-related practices:

ASP.NET Core Identity for authentication
Role-based authorization for Admin pages
[Authorize] for protected user actions
[ValidateAntiForgeryToken] for POST forms
Razor HTML encoding to help protect against XSS
EF Core LINQ queries to avoid raw SQL and reduce SQL injection risk
Ownership checks for editing and deleting posts
Service-level validation against parameter tampering
Custom error pages for common HTTP status codes
AJAX Feature

The like/unlike functionality uses JavaScript fetch() to call a Web API endpoint:

POST /api/likes/toggle/{postId}

The API returns JSON with the updated like state and like count, allowing the page to update without a full reload.

Database

The project uses SQL Server with Entity Framework Core migrations.

If using Docker, start the SQL Server container first:

docker compose up -d

Then apply migrations:

dotnet ef database update --project ChirpNet.Data --startup-project ChirpNet.Web

Run the application:

dotnet run --project ChirpNet.Web
